      "text": "The analysis of the provided spectroscopic and molecular data for sample 8b0a6517-861d-46c9-b750-31b9e6399cf8 leads to the identification of the structure as the protected dipeptide **Boc-Ala-Phe-OtBu** (tert-butyl (tert-butoxycarbonyl)-L-alanyl-L-phenylalaninate).\n\n1.  **Molecular Formula and Unsaturation**: The molecular formula $\\text{C}_{21}\\text{H}_{32}\\text{N}_2\\text{O}_5$ was confirmed by HRMS (found $m/z$ 415.2208 for $[M+Na]^+$, calculated 415.2203). This formula gives a degree of unsaturation (DBE) of 7, corresponding to a benzene ring (4), two amide/ester carbonyls (2), and one carbamate carbonyl (1).\n2.  **$^1\\text{H}$ NMR Interpretation**:\n    *   **Aromatic Region**: Signals at $\\delta$ 7.28–7.13 (5H) represent the monosubstituted benzene ring of a phenylalanine residue.\n    *   **Aliphatic Region**: Two singlets at $\\delta$ 1.42 and 1.38 (9H each) indicate two tert-butyl groups: one from the $N$-terminal Boc group and one from the $C$-terminal tert-butyl ester.\n    *   **Methyl Group**: The doublet at $\\delta$ 1.31 (3H, $J=7.1$ Hz) is the alpha-methyl group of an alanine residue.\n    *   **$\\alpha$-Protons and $\\beta$-Protons**: The multiplet at $\\delta$ 4.72–4.67 (1H) is assigned to the $\\alpha$-CH of phenylalanine, while the signal at $\\delta$ 4.15 (1H) corresponds to the $\\alpha$-CH of alanine. The multiplet at $\\delta$ 3.08–3.06 (2H) corresponds to the benzylic $\\text{CH}_2$ of phenylalanine.\n    *   **NH Protons**: Amide and carbamate NH signals are visible at $\\delta$ 6.58 and 5.06.\n3.  **$^{13}\\text{C}$ NMR Interpretation**: The three carbonyl signals at $\\delta$ 172.21, 170.39, and 155.38 confirm the presence of two peptide-bond/ester-type carbonyls and one Boc carbamate. The peaks at $\\delta$ 82.39 and 80.03 are the quaternary carbons of the tert-butyl groups. The $\\alpha$-carbons appear at $\\delta$ 53.68 and 50.21.\n\nThe chemical shifts and coupling patterns are consistent with the sequence Boc-Ala-Phe-OtBu.\n\nFINAL_RESULT:\n  UUID: 8b0a6517-861d-46c9-b750-31b9e6399cf8\n  PREDICTED_SMILES: CC(C)(C)OC(=O)N[C@@H](C)C(=O)N[C@@H](Cc1ccccc1)C(=O)OC(C)(C)C\n  CONFIDENCE: 0.95\n  REASON_BRIEF: The molecular formula, 1H, and 13C NMR data consistently identify the molecule as a protected dipeptide containing alanine and phenylalanine residues, flanked by a Boc group and a tert-butyl ester. The chemical shifts of the alpha-protons and methyl groups confirm the sequence and identity of the amino acids.",
